properties.name: 1st Home
properties.description: Posted by Tmoon1Deluth, GAI was born in a suburb of Atlanta- Deluth. I lived there till I was 4. From what I remember I always played with Tonka Trucks in the Georgia red clay. Fun Times!!

properties.name: Aunt's House
properties.description: Posted by Tmoon1Hinsdale, ILMy Mother\'s sister lives outside of Chicago in a suburb called Hinsdale. My family stayed at her house 3 times, each time for about a week. She lived near a Ferrari Dealership, so I would go sit for hours and admire the cars.

properties.name: Camp Gorton
properties.description: Posted by Tmoon1Watkins Glen, New YorkI was a Lifeguard at a Boyscout Camp. The camp was on Lake Wanita. I lived up there for a whole Summer. There were many fun and funny times on the lake. My fellow Lifeguards were so funny. We were all very strong swimmers and Lifeguards.

properties.name: Friends Lake House
properties.description: Posted by Tmoon1Graford, TXSome family friends own a lake house on Possum Kingdom Lake, outside of Ft. Worth. I really enjoy this house. This is also where I learned to waterski.

properties.name: Grand Ma's House
properties.description: Posted by Tmoon12502 Wendell Ave. Louisville KYMy Mother\'s Mother. I frequented Louisville, KY. My Grand Ma was very good at cards and could cook like a chef. I always love going to visit her- she is an amazing woman.

properties.name: Holiday Inn Los Angeles International Airport (LAX)
properties.description: Posted by Tmoon1 9901 La Cienega Blvd, CA 90045On a family vacation to the West Coast we stayed at a Holiday Inn near LAX. I thought LA was a very boring city, and I will probablly not go there again unless I have to.
